Limpopo police are offering a reward of 100-thousand rand to anyone with information leading to the arrest of suspects behind the armed robberies at the Letaba and Lebowakgomo Hospitals. Seven suspects broke into a doctors’ residence at the Lebowakgomo hospital and made off with personal items from 11 units. Five suspects shot at and robbed doctors at the Letaba hospital. Two doctors and a nurse were wounded in the attack. Police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo says the task team investigating the crime is making progress… “The police are offering a reward of up to 100 000… Any information received will be treated with confidentiality.” Watch related video:  